Rebuild_CHGLOG: - [arch] mm: pass userspace fault flag to generic fault handler (Johannes Weiner) [1213903] {CVE-2014-8171}
Rebuild_FUZZ: 94.74%
commit-author Johannes Weiner <hannes@cmpxchg.org>
commit 759496ba6407c6994d6a5ce3a5e74937d7816208
Empty-Commit: Cherry-Pick Conflicts during history rebuild.
Will be included in final tarball splat. Ref for failed cherry-pick at:
ciq/ciq_backports/kernel-3.10.0-327.el7/759496ba.failed

Unlike global OOM handling, memory cgroup code will invoke the OOM killer
in any OOM situation because it has no way of telling faults occuring in
kernel context - which could be handled more gracefully - from
user-triggered faults.

Pass a flag that identifies faults originating in user space from the
architecture-specific fault handlers to generic code so that memcg OOM
handling can be improved.

